The United States will host the Ninth Summit of the Americas in Los Angeles, California in June 2022. The summit aims to focus on "Building a Sustainable, Resilient, and Equitable Future" for the Americas. This summit is the only gathering of leaders from North, South, and Central America and the Caribbean. The United States' leadership in the summit process demonstrates their commitment to the Western Hemisphere and the Build Back Better World initiative. The goal of the summit is to bring together leaders and stakeholders to advance shared commitments to economic prosperity, security, human rights, and dignity.